race.comment: MISS DEFY (10) scored an impressive win over 2000m at Canberra two runs ago. Stepped back in trip and was less effective last time when down the track at Wagga. Back in her right race today so expect a return to form. The consistent FULMEN FILOU (4) raced handy then battled on well for second at Armidale recently in a BM58 over 1900m. Might need some luck from the wide gate but he is a genuine gelding who is sure to give a good account. AKAUWHEO (7) led for the judge but was swamped in the straight over 1800m at Gilgandra last time. Down in class and a bit less pressure over today's journey will help. EJECT (9) found the line well at Armidale last start and the extra trip today looks a plus. DESCENDING MIST (1) hasn't been all that far away of late and this is a drop in grade on recent efforts. Looks a chance with the help of the 4kg claim.
